,"n8935","n8936","n8937"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dream (something) or about [with بِ (bi)] (something) while asleep","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dream (something) or about [with بِ (bi)] (something) while asleep; to muse, reflect, or meditate on [with بِ (bi)]; to vision, to image","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience the first seminal ejaculation; to mature physically or sexually; to attain puberty","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience the first seminal ejaculation; to become a legal adult or to be perceived as such","tags":["archaic","intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mature mentally or to be perceived as such; to act or think like an adult","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be gentle, forgiving, merciful, or lenient; to be mild-mannered","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to restrain oneself or to be restrained or checked (especially emotionally and psychologically); to forbear, to refrain, to abstain, to withhold; to be long-suffering, to be patient or enduring; to mellow","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَمَ (ḥalama) (form I): dreaming","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a dream (something experienced during sleep); vision"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a wish, a desire, an aspiration; a daydream (something fantasised about or desired)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"utopia"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَمَ (ḥalama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sexual maturity; puberty","examples":[{"text":"وَإِذَا بَلَغَ ٱلْأَطْفَالُ مِنْكُمُ ٱلْحُلُمَ فَلْيَسْتَأْذِنُوا كَمَا ٱسْتَأْذَنَ ٱلَّذِينَ مِنْ قَبْلِهِمْ","english":"And if the children among you reach puberty, they shall ask for permission as those who did before them."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلُمَ (ḥaluma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mental, psychological, or comportmental maturity; prudence; rationality; discretion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"being long-suffering, self-restraint; forbearance, longanimity","examples":[{"text":"أَنْتَ أَكْثَرُ مِنِّي حِلْمًا.","english":"You are more patient than me."},{"text":"لَا يَغُرَّنَّكَ حِلْمِي فَصَبْرِي بَدَأَ يَنْفَدُ.","english":"Let not my forbearance deceive you, for my patience is running out."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tick(s), mite(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nipple(s), teat(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"callous-leaved gromwell (Moltkiopsis ciliata)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Akin to Aramaic חֶלְמָא (ḥelmā), Classical Syriac ܚܠܡܐ (ḥelmā), Hebrew חֲלוֹם (ḥalóm), Amharic ሕልም (ḥəlm), Ugaritic 𐎈𐎍𐎎 (ḥlm). For the significations of the root in Arabic, compare م ن ي (m n y), whence أُمْنِيَة (ʔumniya, “a wish”) and مَنِيّ (maniyy, “a fluid considered conceptive; semen”)."},"ipa":["/ħulm/","/ħu.lum/"]}